<subSubSection pageId="86" pageNumber="2316" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="86.[160,1155,1460,1727]" pageId="86" pageNumber="2316">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,282,1460,1485]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="2316">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
this species is separated from other in the group by the following combined characters: clypeo-genal angulation obtuse (120³) (as 
<emphasis box="[827,1094,1495,1519]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="2316">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haroldi" authorityYear="1867" box="[827,927,1495,1519]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pinotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="2316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fissus">D. fissus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Luederwaldt" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[948,1094,1495,1519]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="2316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spadiceus">D. spadiceus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haroldi" authorityYear="1869" box="[160,284,1530,1554]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pinotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="2316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ascanius">
<emphasis box="[160,284,1530,1554]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="2316">D. ascanius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); pronotal disc having a central-rounded lobe on the anterior portion of disc (as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Vaz-de-Mello" authorityYear="2019" box="[200,331,1565,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="2316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbarae">
<emphasis box="[200,331,1565,1589]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="2316">D. barbarae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); pronotum with coarse deeply impressed punctures along the anterior e posterior margin (as 
<emphasis box="[419,682,1599,1623]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="2316">
<taxonomicName box="[419,534,1599,1623]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="2316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="darwini">D. darwini</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Vaz-de-Mello" authorityYear="2019" box="[547,682,1599,1623]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="2316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="filgueirasi">D. filgueirasi</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Luederwaldti" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[742,845,1599,1623]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="2316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ingens">
<emphasis box="[742,845,1599,1623]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="2316">D. ingens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); cephalic horn rounded at apex (as 
<taxonomicName box="[259,375,1634,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pinotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="2316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicuspis">
<emphasis box="[259,375,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="2316">D. bicuspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); paramera with parallel-rounded apexes (as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harold" authorityYear="1869" box="[883,983,1634,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pinotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="2316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reichei">
<emphasis box="[883,983,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="2316">D. reichei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and paramera (on lateral view) with inferior margin smoothı lacking emarginations near the junction with phalobasis.
</paragraph>
