<subSubSection pageId="87" pageNumber="2317" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="87.[160,1156,253,936]" pageId="87" pageNumber="2317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,301,253,278]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="2317">Description.</emphasis>
colour: blackı shiny. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[544,606,254,278]" pageId="87" pageNumber="2317">Head</emphasis>
: dorsal surface smooth except for ocellate punctures posterior to cephalic horn. Gena borders slightly curved inward. Clypeo-genal junction obtuse (120³). Cephalic carina conical rounded at apex. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[931,1051,323,347]" pageId="87" pageNumber="2317">Pronotum</emphasis>
: borders smoothı not serratedı flattened at sides. Ocellate punctures evenly spaced present at anterior portion. Posterior margin bearing two to three rows of ocellate punctures. Pronotal disc smoothı shinyı lacking punctures and having a central lobe on the anterior portion of disc. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[339,499,462,486]" pageId="87" pageNumber="2317">Metasternum</emphasis>
: sides and margins of anterior lobe with setigerous punctures. Anterior portion of anterior lobe glabrous with chagrinated microsculpture. Setigerous punctures equally spaced at sides. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[705,774,531,555]" pageId="87" pageNumber="2317">Elytra</emphasis>
: striae deeply impressed having very fine punctures (never larger than striae) spaced 3-four times their diameter. Interstriae convex. Interstriae disc lacking microsculpture with very fine punctures (20 x). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,313,635,659]" pageId="87" pageNumber="2317">Abdomen</emphasis>
: sides of each ventrite excavated with many ocellate punctures concentrated at sides. Some of these punctures with very short and scattered hair. Puncture of each ventrite interrupted medially as well as groove along the posterior margin of sixth ventrite. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[270,388,739,763]" pageId="87" pageNumber="2317">Aedeagus</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[413,531,739,763]" captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="50.[160,225,1682,1705]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1634]" captionTargetId="figure@50.[163,1153,142,1650]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="Figure 35. D. blancoi: (a) male dorsal habitus; (b) paramera dorsal view; (c) paramera ventral view; (d) paramera lateral view; (e) detail of the carena found on the middle of paramera longitudinal excavation. D. candangoi: (f) male dorsal habitus; (g) paramera dorsal view; (h) paramera ventral view; (i) paramera lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3665585" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3665585/files/figure.png" pageId="87" pageNumber="2317">Figure 35</figureCitation>
(g-i)): Dorsallyı paramere apexes truncatedı parallel. Longitudinal excavation taking 2/3 of paramera longitudinal length; basal excavations rounded. Laterallyı subtle declivity from basis towards apex; posterior margin smoothı at most slightly sinuated and lacking emarginations near the junction with phalobasis. Ventrallyı each paramera bearing a transversal basal groove. Subgenital plate emarginated both apically and basally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
